A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a massive filing cabinet stretching impossibly tall into a warm amber sky, with hundreds of manila folders cascading down like a waterfall into an open briefcase at the bottom. Small paper airplanes made from documents swirl around the cabinet in a spiral pattern. The scene has a retro color palette of mustard yellow, burnt orange, and teal, with halftone dot textures and slightly faded edges reminiscent of mid-century magazine advertisements. The briefcase sits on a checkered floor, overflowing with neatly stacked papers, suggesting successful collection and organization of abundant materials.
